A vintage 1950s-style illustration of a well-dressed businessman lounging in an overstuffed armchair, feet propped up on a towering, precarious stack of manila folders and papers, while casually glancing at an ornate wall clock showing 11:55. The room features warm amber tones, wood-paneled walls, and a large window showing a sunset. On a nearby desk, an elaborate filing system with color-coded tabs sits perfectly organized but untouched. The man holds a steaming coffee cup with a satisfied, slightly mischievous expression. Dust motes float in golden light beams. The aesthetic channels mid-century advertising art with rich, saturated colors and slightly exaggerated proportions.
